    "summary": "Chemical Engineer with fifteen years of professional experience as Process and Control Process Engineer. My experience has been developed in operations of heavy oil desalter plant. Experience with process equipment and systems field installation, commissioning and testing, as well as troubleshooting process equipment and systems failures, including pumps, fiscal metering, pipe line/piping, and dehydration systems. Strong experience with SCADA and DCS systems.\n\nThe highlights skills are:\n\n- Experience in operation and configuration SCADA ABB and Wonderware systems.\n- Experience as Plant Process Engineer: Scheduled shutdowns, make improvements in process plant equipment.\n- Develops to perform process engineering activities in conceptual and basic phases of a project.\n- Extensive knowledge in SIL/SIF and HAZOPs analysis.\n- Improve process capability and production volume while maintaining and improving quality standards.\n- Collect, record, and transcribe data.\n- Show results in reports.\n- Provide suggestions during incident investigations.\n- Advise on corrective actions.\n- Work with equipment designers and manufacturing officers to develop a cost-effective and working production process.\n- Ensure projects are completed on time.\n- Research and purchase new process technology.\n- Collecting data required to make improvements and/or modifications\n- Overseeing the construction of new plants\n- Supervising plant operations\n- Investigating and troubleshooting plant/process problems\n- Ensuring that equipment works to its specification and to appropriate capacities\n- Assessing safety and environmental issues",
